cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with training neural networks subject to a Lipschitz constraint, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of Lipschitz functions for provable adversarial robustness (cs.NE), and the estimation of Wasserstein distance (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a new activation function (GroupSort) and discusses its use in achieving provable adversarial robustness (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the preservation of gradient norms during backpropagation, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
